theorem Topology.interior_diff_subset_diff_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    interior (A \ B) ⊆ interior A \ closure B := by
  classical
  intro x hx
  -- Step 1: from `x ∈ interior (A \ B)` we get `x ∈ interior A`.
  have hxIntA : x ∈ interior A := by
    have h_subset : (A \ B) ⊆ A := Set.diff_subset
    exact (interior_mono h_subset) hx
  -- Step 2: prove `x ∉ closure B`.
  have hxNotClB : x ∉ closure B := by
    by_contra hxClB
    -- Unpack the neighbourhood information coming from `hx`.
    rcases mem_interior_iff_mem_nhds.1 hx with ⟨U, hUopen, hxU, hUsub⟩
    -- Since `x ∈ closure B`, every neighbourhood of `x` meets `B`.
    have h_nonempty : (U ∩ B).Nonempty :=
      (mem_closure_iff).1 hxClB U hUopen hxU
    rcases h_nonempty with ⟨y, hyU, hyB⟩
    -- But `U ⊆ A \ B`, hence `y ∉ B`, contradiction.
    have : y ∈ A \ B := hUsub hyU
    exact (this.2) hyB
  exact And.intro hxIntA hxNotClB

theorem Topology.closure_diff_subset_closure_diff {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    closure (A \ B) ⊆ closure A \ interior B := by
  intro x hx
  -- First, note that `A \ B ⊆ A`, so taking closures preserves this inclusion.
  have hxClA : x ∈ closure A :=
    (closure_mono (Set.diff_subset : A \ B ⊆ A)) hx
  -- Next, we show that `x ∉ interior B`.
  have hxNotIntB : x ∉ interior B := by
    intro hxIntB
    -- Because `x ∈ closure (A \ B)`, every open neighbourhood of `x`
    -- intersects `A \ B`.  In particular, this holds for `interior B`,
    -- which is an open set containing `x`.
    have h_nonempty : (interior B ∩ (A \ B)).Nonempty := by
      have h_open : IsOpen (interior B) := isOpen_interior
      exact (mem_closure_iff).1 hx (interior B) h_open hxIntB
    -- Extract a point `y` witnessing the non-emptiness.
    rcases h_nonempty with ⟨y, ⟨hyIntB, hyDiff⟩⟩
    -- From `y ∈ interior B` we obtain `y ∈ B`.
    have hyB : y ∈ B := interior_subset hyIntB
    -- But `y ∈ A \ B` means `y ∉ B`, yielding a contradiction.
    exact hyDiff.2 hyB
  -- Assemble the result.
  exact And.intro hxClA hxNotIntB

theorem Topology.interior_closure_eq_univ_iff_dense {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure A) = (Set.univ : Set X) ↔ closure A = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  constructor
  · intro hInt
    have h_subset : (Set.univ : Set X) ⊆ closure A := by
      have h_incl : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
      simpa [hInt] using h_incl
    exact Set.Subset.antisymm (Set.Subset_univ _) h_subset
  · intro hCl
    have hIntEq : interior (closure A) = interior (Set.univ : Set X) :=
      congrArg (fun s : Set X => interior s) hCl
    simpa [interior_univ] using hIntEq

theorem Topology.closure_interior_subset_closure_interior_union
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (A ∪ B)) := by
  -- First, note the inclusion `A ⊆ A ∪ B`, and pass to interiors.
  have h : interior A ⊆ interior (A ∪ B) :=
    interior_mono (Set.subset_union_left : A ⊆ A ∪ B)
  -- Taking closures preserves set inclusion.
  exact closure_mono h
